metadata.name: Forced Ink #59
metadata.description:
Forced Ink is an experiment in using physical forces (repulsion) to create digital artwork reminiscent of a real-world abstract painting.

Features
Color: a random color
Particle Count: between 100 and 450, equal chance
Particle Size: between 5 and 15, equal chance

metadata.name: Infinite Scaling System #72
metadata.description:
This generative system has a beginning, but no ending. It scales infinitely in different directions as unlimited shapes are added. Special care was taken to avoid memory overflows, impossibly big numbers, and poor performance. 

Rendered using P5.JS

metadata.name: Negative Space #9
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: Deconstructions #66
metadata.description:
Deconstructions is a further experiment with blending 3 colors and 3 different textures to create structural/abstract compositions. It's a search for beauty within asymmetrical/unsynchronized forms and disharmonic structures.


Probabilities;

- 18 compositions with variations.

- 2 background colors.

- 3 different particle starting placements.

- 21 different base color palettes. (1 monochrome) 

- 2 different alpha types; tangential & randomized.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).

Additional animation features with different shapes, angles, direction and style.

metadata.name: Boids 2D #152
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: overloaded #101
metadata.description: Overloaded attempts to be a system to explore time perception, through non-representative images, while still representing pixels as upscaled forms. It plays with permanence and non-permanence.

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #205
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License
Runs properly on Chrome 97.0.4692.99
GPU intensive
